OL,3,CCampaign group loses bid to challenge
OL,4,Cplans to upgrade A66
OL,6,FBut Mr Justice Mould said the
OL,7,Ftransport secretary in the previous
OL,8,FConservative government, Mark Harper,
OL,9,F"found a compelling need for the
OL,10,Fdevelopment to take place" and
OL,11,F"considered whether there were any
OL,12,Falternatives which might serve to
OL,13,Fachieve that compelling need".
OL,15,FA spokesperson for National Highways
OL,16,Fsaid: "The legal challenge to the A66
OL,17,FNorthern Trans-Pennine upgrade has
OL,18,Fbeen rejected at the High Court. We
OL,19,Fwill update on next steps in due
OL,20,Fcourse."
